The '''Qinding Xianfa Dagang''' of 1908 ({{zh|c=[[wikt:钦定|欽定]][[wikt:宪法|憲法]][[wikt:大纲|大綱]]|p=Qīndìng Xiànfǎ Dàgāng|l=Outline of Constitution by Imperial Order" or "Outline of Imperial Constitution}}, also translated as the '''Principles of the Constitution'''<ref>Mongolia in the Twentieth Century: Landlocked Cosmopolitan, pp. 41</ref>) is the late [[Qing dynasty]] attempt to establish a [[constitutional monarchy]] country at the beginning of the 20th century. It was modeled on the Japanese [[Meiji Constitution]].

